name: Okanagan
description:
I didn't sleep much last night. About 4 hours probably, so my energy was really low all day. 

We decided to head north after some warnings about the climb out of Osoyoos, and the heat wave forecast. Unfortunately, it's hard to out-bike a heat wave, so we still had a sweaty one. I'm still averaging about 5 litres of water a day.

We had lunch in Penticton and met up with Andrew from Cychotic bikes in St. John's. He lives in Kelowna and offered us a crash in his basement which we gladly accepted to escape the heat. He also took our panniers from Penticton to Kelowna so that we could ride a lot faster and enjoyably for the afternoon.
